						<summary>

						<p>This records an endowment of half a <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> and 4 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land for maintaining 5 musicians who were to play on instruments during the <hi rend="italic">śrībali</hi> service every day in the temple, by <hi rend="bold">Kaṟpaga-Āditaṉ Āśaṉ Amudaṉakkaṉ</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">madhyastha</hi> of the village. The <hi rend="italic">mahā-sabhā</hi> made this land tax-free.</p>						

						</summary>
